The paper proposes a long-term memory design for artificial general intelligence, which falls under the category of AI. The focus of the paper is on incremental machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (LG). The use of Stochastic Context Free Grammar and programming idioms suggests a connection to natural language processing (NE) and programming languages (PL). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of their approach through experiments, which suggests a connection to software engineering (SE).
